feedback: I've never been a part of a study like this, thank you for your opportunity. I send my greetings to the artists, the ones who performed and also who made the movie. Their work is important, fighting for this cause is something we all should be grateful for.

I am really inspired and moved by the performance. both the artist(professor) gave their best and the performance was flawless that gives you an idea about to what extent they have gone just to portray the scenarios. I would like to thank Shreshth Saxena for inviting me to this event.

I found the background and research used to create the songs in the documentary very powerful, and knowing the explanations made the performance more emotional, as well as the tie in to an actual exoneree, even if from a creative stand point I found both pieces a bit long.
